article.headline: Arkansas St. 76, Western Ky. 75
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Adrian Banks scored 27 points, including the winning layup with 10 seconds remaining, and Arkansas State beat Western Kentucky 76-75 Thursday night. Boris Siakam had given the Hilltoppers (15-7, 7-3 Sun Belt) a one-point lead with two free throws with 22 seconds to play. Isaac Wells added 20 points for the Indians, who overcame a 13-point first-half deficit. Arkansas State (11-10, 6-3) outscored Western Kentucky in the paint 36-20. Courtney Lee led the balanced Hilltoppers with 15 points. Tyrone Brazelton scored 14, and Siakam was one of three Western Kentucky players with 12. Ryan Wedel had 13 points, six rebounds and five assists for Arkansas State, and Shawn Morgan added 10 points and eight rebounds. Banks scored 20 of his points in the second half. Western Kentucky led 37-33 at halftime after 11 first-half offensive rebounds. Arkansas State responded with nine offensive rebounds in the second half.
